            personally would lead me to one piece of advice above all others - always have a cap on you. But again, I have no
            idea if this would hold for anyone else. I struggle a lot with light. I'm blind in one eye, and in the other have 
            a reduced field of vision around the edges and a blind spot running diagonially across more-or-less the middle. 
            </p>
            <p>
            But also I think everything is a bit darker for me. Sometimes I struggle to read something, even in a well-lit room, but 
            if I put a headtorch on, suddenly it's not a problem. There's just never enough light hitting where I need it to 
            inside, it seems. But outside, the opposite then becomes true and I am very easily blinded. Hence, the hat.        
