              <h3>Hats And Sunglasses</h3>
              <p>
                I wanted to talk about  this because many people seem to gravitate towards sunglasses, and I do use them too 
                and they certainly do help, 
                but if I had to choose between the two, I'd definitely choose the hat, without it sometimes I simply can't see
                anything walking towards the sun. My current favourite cap is 
                <a href="https://www.sundayafternoons.co.uk/collections/mens/products/vaporlite-stride-cap?variant=42021736186009">The Vaporlite Stride Cap</a>
                from Sunday Afternoons. </p>
                <p>
                I have several hats from this manufacturer and they are <em>really</em> well designed.
                They use exceptional fabrics that are light, breathable, and wick away sweat quickly and effectively. They have 
                , in my opinion, the best type of adjustment which is the buckle style where you can just pull one-handed to 
                tighten it (see photo to 
                the left), which is excellent for sudden gusts of wind that threaten to take your hat away. The closure s
                ystem also has 
                a bit of elastic in it which means the fit is stretchable and therefore never uncomfortable, and lots of their hats, 
                including this one, have reflective detailing on them - something I consider a massive selling point due to my almost 
                non-existant night vision.
              </p>
            </div>
