                lens is probably a better everyday lens since I find the Oakley one a bit dark in a lot of situations.
              </p>
              <p>
                Oakley have a lens called Prizm Daily Polarized which is a bit lighter than the black version and is probably 
                the most directly comparable to Sungod Slate - so much so that when I got my Sungods I put the pair of Oakleys 
                I had with Prizm Daily on ebay because looking through the lenses was so similar that I found them redundant. 
                I don't think they make this model with that lens though, so you'd have to get a custom pair to get that and 
                that can get very expensive (if it's even an option they offer - this can change with time). But regardless 
                of which lens you go with, this is an excellent pair of glasses.
